race.comment: HOT CHIPS (1) debuts at home and is a capable galloper well-placed with the 3kg claim. She's capable of using the inside barrier and has jumped out well. Looks ready to go and rates to be in the finish. SKY SISTA (5) draws out but is right up to this if presented on song. She's raced well in stronger metro contests and has a jumpout under the saddle. The betting will be key. MAGIC MONEY (3) resumed much improved, winning his Maiden this track/distance. Has an awkward barrier, but won't have to improve much to get some of the money.MISSILE GIRL (7) settled last at Geelong in a 66 and endured a tough run. He'd just missed this grade/track/distance prior, and that's a better indicator of her chances. She usually makes it hard for herself, but can be in the finish if things work out.
